From 47bbc383e55060f176383bcdf9a4e891b9da21c8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.local>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 08:20:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 3 (manual): real sender usernames + manual reply
 sending

- Webhook now fetches the sender's real name/username via Instagram's
  Graph API on the first message from a new conversation, replacing
  the 'Instagram user xxxxxx' placeholder. Self-heals on a later
  message if the initial lookup fails (best-effort, never blocks
  message processing).
- New POST /api/inbox/conversations/[id]/messages route sends a
  reply through Instagram's Send API and persists it as an 'agent'
  message on success.
- Chat panel's reply box is now fully wired: type, send, optimistic
  UI update, inline error display on failure (e.g. Instagram
  disconnected, empty conversation-sender mapping).
- Inbox view lifts conversation state up so a sent message updates
  the list preview and timestamp immediately without a full refetch.
